<DOC><DOCNO> AP901220-0224 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-12-20-90 1336EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Britain-PollyPeck     12-20 0204</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Britain-Polly Peck,0215</SECOND><HEAD>Polly Peck Chief Freed on Bail</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Asil Nadir, chief executive of troubled Polly PeckInternational PLC, was freed Thursday on $6.8 million bail afterspending five nights in jail.   James Perriss, governor of London's Wormwood Scrubbs Prison,confirmed the release of Nadir, a 48-year-old Turkish-Cypriotbusinessman who was arrested Saturday.   He faces 18 charges of theft and false accounting in connectionwith the affairs of his troubled fruit and electronicsconglomerate.   One of his attorneys, Peter Knight, said Nadir would strenuouslyfight the charges of false accounting and theft of an alleged $48million between June 1988 and July 1990.   Nadir is required to live and sleep at his London address and toreport daily to a police stationm, according to terms set by amagistrate. The businessman also had to surrender his passport andwas barred from buying travel tickets.   Scotland Yard's fraud squad in recent months has beeninvestigating alleged irregularities in share dealings in PollyPeck.   The company was turned over to court-appointed administrators inOctober after its shares collapsed on the London Stock Exchange.The administrators are trying to sort out the company's $2.5billion in debt while it continues to operate under courtprotection from creditors.</TEXT></DOC>